article.headline: Indiana St. 84, Drake 73
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- Marico Stinson scored 37 points -- including a school-record nine 3-pointers -- to lead Indiana State over Drake 84-73 Saturday night in a Missouri Valley Conference game. Stinson, a freshman, was 14-of-17. Cole Holmstrom had career highs with 20 points and six assists. Gabe Moore had 16 points, including 8-of-8 free throws. The Sycamores (8-4, 1-1 MVC) overcame a 17-point first-half deficit but still trailed 41-38 at the break. Stinson had five 3-pointers in the first half and Indiana State went 17-of-26 from 3-point range for the game. Ajay Calvin led Drake (9-4, 0-2 MVC) with 17 points and 10 rebounds. Klayton Korver had 15 points, including four 3-pointers. Chris Bryant scored 10 points.
